The paper deals with the problem of sorting objects using a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves using RGBD images to predict the class of objects being picked up, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The system also involves a controller to learn a mapping from the image to the predicted result, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
